# Paths Kage should treat as non-knowledge: never index them into the code graph,
# never let memory be grounded to them, and never mark memory stale because they
# changed or were deleted. Patterns ending in "/" match a whole directory.

# The viewer is a presentation/visualization layer, not knowledge-bearing source.
# Memory packets describe repo logic and decisions; they should never be anchored
# to viewer markup/scripts.
mcp/viewer/
docs/viewer/
